The paper deals with the coordination problem of multiple robots, which is a typical problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a nature-inspired approach and an analytical mathematical model to solve the problem, which involves decision making and optimization, indicating the relevance of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also emphasizes the cooperation and coordination among the robots, which is a typical problem in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY).
